BASIC EARNINGS PER SHARE IS CALCULATED BY THE SUM OF (1) NET EARNINGS LESS DECLARED DIVIDENDS AND DIVIDEND EQUIVALENTS RELATED

TO SHARE-BASED COMPENSATION DIVIDED BY THE BASIC WEIGHTED AVERAGE SHARES OUTSTANDING AND (2) DECLARED DIVIDENDS AND DIVIDEND EQUIVALENTS RELATED TO SHARE-BASED COMPENSATION DIVIDED BY THE WEIGHTED AVERAGE SHARES OUTSTANDING.

